Commands.Name: bucket-create
Commands.Description: Create a new bucket
Commands.Usage: bucket-create --bucket BUCKET_NAME [--ibm-service-instance-id ID] [--class CLASS_NAME] [--region REGION] --kms-root-key-crn CUSTOMERROOTKEYCRN --kms-encryption-algorithm ALGORITHM [--output FORMAT] [--json]

Flags.Name: bucket
Flags.Description: The name (`BUCKET_NAME`) of the bucket.

Flags.Name: ibm-service-instance-id
Flags.Description: Sets the IBM Service Instance `ID` in the request.

Flags.Name: class
Flags.Description: The name (`CLASS_NAME`) of the Class.

Flags.Name: region
Flags.Description: The `REGION` where the bucket is present. If this flag is not provided, the program will use the default option specified in config.

Flags.Name: kms-root-key-crn
Flags.Description: The `CUSTOMERROOTKEYCRN` of the KMS  root key associated with the bucket for data encryption.

Flags.Name: kms-encryption-algorithm
Flags.Description: The `ALGORITHM` and `SIZE` to use with the encryption key stored by using key protect.

Flags.Name: output
Flags.Description: Output `FORMAT` can be only json or text.

Flags.Name: json
Flags.Description: [Deprecated] Output returned in raw JSON format.

Flags.Description: The `SIZE` of each page to get in the service call. This does not affect the number of items returned in the command's output. Commands.Name: object-get
Commands.Description: Download an object from a bucket
Commands.Usage: object-get --bucket BUCKET_NAME --key KEY [--if-match ETAG] [--if-modified-since TIMESTAMP] [--if-none-match ETAG] [--if-unmodified-since TIMESTAMP] [--range RANGE] [--response-cache-control HEADER] [--response-content-disposition HEADER] [--response-content-encoding HEADER] [--response-content-language HEADER] [--response-content-type HEADER] [--response-expires HEADER] [--region REGION] [--version-id value] [--output FORMAT] [--json] [OUTFILE]

Flags.Name: bucket
Flags.Description: The name (`BUCKET_NAME`) of the bucket.

Flags.Name: key
Flags.Description: The `KEY` of the object.

Flags.Name: if-match
Flags.Description: Return the object only if its entitytag (ETag) is the same as the `ETAG` specified, otherwise return a 412 (precondition failed).

Flags.Name: if-modified-since
Flags.Description: Return the object only if it has been modified since the specified `TIMESTAMP`, otherwise return a 304 (not modified).

Flags.Name: if-none-match
Flags.Description: Return the object only if its entity tag(ETag) is different from the `ETAG` specified, otherwise return a 304 (not modified).

Flags.Name: if-unmodified-since
Flags.Description: Return the object only if it has not been modified since the specified `TIMESTAMP`, otherwise return a 412 (precondition failed).

Flags.Name: range
Flags.Description: Downloads the specified `RANGE` bytes of an object. For more information about the HTTP Range header, go to http://www.w3.org/Protocols/rfc2616/rfc2616-sec14.html#sec14.35.

Flags.Name: response-cache-control
Flags.Description: Sets the Cache-Control `HEADER` of the response.

Flags.Name: response-content-disposition
Flags.Description: Sets the Content-Disposition `HEADER` of the response.

Flags.Name: response-content-encoding
Flags.Description: Sets the Content-Encoding `HEADER` of the response.

Flags.Name: response-content-language
Flags.Description: Sets the Content-Language `HEADER` of the response.

Flags.Name: response-content-type
Flags.Description: Sets the Content-Type `HEADER` of the response.

Flags.Name: response-expires
Flags.Description: Sets the Expires `HEADER` of the response.

Flags.Name: region
Flags.Description: The `REGION` where the bucket is present. If this flag is not provided, the program will use the default option specified in config.

Flags.Name: version-id
Flags.Description: The object version identifier

Flags.Name: output
Flags.Description: Output `FORMAT` can be only json or text.

Flags.Name: json
Flags.Description: [Deprecated] Output returned in raw JSON format.

Commands.Name: object-put
Commands.Description: Upload an object to a bucket
Commands.Usage: object-put --bucket BUCKET_NAME --key KEY [--body FILE_PATH] [--cache-control CACHING_DIRECTIVES] [--content-disposition DIRECTIVES] [--content-encoding CONTENT_ENCODING] [--content-language LANGUAGE] [--content-length SIZE] [--content-md5 MD5] [--content-type MIME] [--metadata STRUCTURE] [--tagging Key1=Value1] [--website-redirect-location LOCATION] [--region REGION] [--output FORMAT] [--json]

Flags.Name: bucket
Flags.Description: The name (`BUCKET_NAME`) of the bucket.

Flags.Name: key
Flags.Description: The `KEY` of the object.

Flags.Name: body
Flags.Description: Object data location (`FILE_PATH`).

Flags.Name: cache-control
Flags.Description: Specifies `CACHING_DIRECTIVES` for the request/reply chain.

Flags.Name: content-disposition
Flags.Description: Specifies presentational information (`DIRECTIVES`).

Flags.Name: content-encoding
Flags.Description: Specifies what content encodings (`CONTENT_ENCODING`) have been applied to the object and thus what decoding mechanisms must be applied to obtain the media-type referenced by the Content-Type header field.

Flags.Name: content-language
Flags.Description: The `LANGUAGE` the content is in.

Flags.Name: content-length
Flags.Description: `SIZE` of the body in bytes. This parameter is useful when the size of the body cannot be determined automatically.

Flags.Name: content-md5
Flags.Description: The base64-encoded 128-bit `MD5` digest of the data.

Flags.Name: content-type
Flags.Description: A standard `MIME` type describing the format of the object data.

Flags.Name: metadata
Flags.Description: A `STRUCTURE` using JSON syntax. See IBM Cloud Documentation.

Flags.Name: tagging
Flags.Description: A tag-set for the object encoded as URL query parameters (`Key1=Value1`). For `object-tagging-put`, a `STRUCTURE` using JSON syntax. See IBM Cloud Documentation.

Flags.Name: website-redirect-location
Flags.Description: If a bucket is configured as a website, redirects requests for the object key to another object in the same bucket or to a URL (`LOCATION`).

Flags.Name: region
Flags.Description: The `REGION` where the bucket is present. If this flag is not provided, the program will use the default option specified in config.

Flags.Name: output
Flags.Description: Output `FORMAT` can be only json or text.

Flags.Name: json
Flags.Description: [Deprecated] Output returned in raw JSON format.

Commands.Name: object-copy
Commands.Description: Copy an object from one bucket to another
Commands.Usage: object-copy --bucket BUCKET_NAME --key KEY --copy-source SOURCE [--cache-control CACHING_DIRECTIVES] [--content-disposition DIRECTIVES] [--content-encoding CONTENT_ENCODING] [--content-language LANGUAGE] [--content-type MIME] [--copy-source-if-match ETAG] [--copy-source-if-modified-since TIMESTAMP] [--copy-source-if-none-match ETAG] [--copy-source-if-unmodified-since TIMESTAMP] [--metadata STRUCTURE] [--metadata-directive DIRECTIVE] [--tagging Key1=Value1] [--tagging-directive value] [--website-redirect-location LOCATION] [--region REGION] [--output FORMAT] [--json]

Flags.Name: bucket
Flags.Description: The name (`BUCKET_NAME`) of the bucket.

Flags.Name: key
Flags.Description: The `KEY` of the object.

Flags.Name: copy-source
Flags.Description: (`SOURCE`) The name of the source bucket and key name of the source object, separated by a slash (/). Must be URL-encoded.

Flags.Name: cache-control
Flags.Description: Specifies `CACHING_DIRECTIVES` for the request/reply chain.

Flags.Name: content-disposition
Flags.Description: Specifies presentational information (`DIRECTIVES`).

Flags.Name: content-encoding
Flags.Description: Specifies what content encodings (`CONTENT_ENCODING`) have been applied to the object and thus what decoding mechanisms must be applied to obtain the media-type referenced by the Content-Type header field.

Flags.Name: content-language
Flags.Description: The `LANGUAGE` the content is in.

Flags.Name: content-type
Flags.Description: A standard `MIME` type describing the format of the object data.

Flags.Name: copy-source-if-match
Flags.Description: Copies the object if its entity tag (Etag) matches the specified tag (`ETAG`).

Flags.Name: copy-source-if-modified-since
Flags.Description: Copies the object if it has been modified since the specified time (`TIMESTAMP`).

Flags.Name: copy-source-if-none-match

Commands.Name: list-multipart-uploads
Commands.Description: List active multipart uploads
Commands.Usage: list-multipart-uploads --bucket BUCKET_NAME [--delimiter DELIMITER] [--encoding-type METHOD] [--prefix PREFIX] [--key-marker value] [--upload-id-marker value] [--page-size SIZE] [--max-items NUMBER] [--region REGION] [--output FORMAT] [--json]

Flags.Name: bucket
Flags.Description: The name (`BUCKET_NAME`) of the bucket.

Flags.Name: delimiter
Flags.Description: A `DELIMITER` is a character you use to group keys.

Flags.Name: encoding-type
Flags.Description: Requests to encode the object keys in the response and specifies the encoding `METHOD` to use.

Flags.Name: prefix
Flags.Description: Limits the response to keys that begin with the specified `PREFIX`.

Flags.Name: key-marker
Flags.Description: Together with another listing parameter, specifies the key from which to start listing

Flags.Name: upload-id-marker
Flags.Description: Together with key-marker, specifies the multipart upload after which listing should begin. If key-marker is not specified, the upload-id-marker parameter is ignored.

Flags.Name: page-size
Flags.Description: The `SIZE` of each page to get in the service call. This does not affect the number of items returned in the command's output. Setting a smaller page size results in more calls to the COS service, retrieving fewer items in each call. This can help prevent the service calls from timing out.

Flags.Name: max-items
Flags.Description: The total `NUMBER` of items to return in the command's output.

Flags.Name: region
Flags.Description: The `REGION` where the bucket is present. If this flag is not provided, the program will use the default option specified in config.

Flags.Name: output
Flags.Description: Output `FORMAT` can be only json or text.

Flags.Name: json
Flags.Description: [Deprecated] Output returned in raw JSON format.

Flags.Name: bucket

Flags.Name: key

Flags.Name: upload-id

Flags.Name: part-number

Flags.Name: content-length

Flags.Name: body
Flags.Description: Object data location (`FILE_PATH`).

Flags.Name: region
Flags.Description: The `REGION` where the bucket is present. If this flag is not provided, the program will use the default option specified in config.

Flags.Name: output

Commands.Name: upload-part-copy
Commands.Description: Upload a part by copying data from an existing object
Commands.Usage: upload-part-copy --bucket BUCKET_NAME --key KEY --upload-id ID --part-number NUMBER --copy-source SOURCE [--copy-source-if-match ETAG] [--copy-source-if-modified-since TIMESTAMP] [--copy-source-if-none-match ETAG] [--copy-source-if-unmodified-since TIMESTAMP] [--copy-source-range value] [--region REGION] [--output FORMAT] [--json]

Flags.Name: bucket
Flags.Description: The name (`BUCKET_NAME`) of the bucket.

Flags.Name: key
Flags.Description: The `KEY` of the object.

Flags.Name: upload-id
Flags.Description: Upload `ID` identifying the multipart upload.

Flags.Name: part-number
Flags.Description: Part `NUMBER` of part being uploaded. This is a positive integer between 1 and 10,000.

Flags.Name: copy-source
Flags.Description: (`SOURCE`) The name of the source bucket and key name of the source object, separated by a slash (/). Must be URL-encoded.

Flags.Name: copy-source-if-match
Flags.Description: Copies the object if its entity tag (Etag) matches the specified tag (`ETAG`).

Flags.Name: copy-source-if-modified-since
Flags.Description: Copies the object if it has been modified since the specified time (`TIMESTAMP`).

Flags.Name: copy-source-if-none-match
Flags.Description: Copies the object if its entity tag (ETag) is different than the specified tag (`ETAG`).

Flags.Name: copy-source-if-unmodified-since
Flags.Description: Copies the object if it hasn't been modified since the specified time (`TIMESTAMP`).

Flags.Name: copy-source-range
Flags.Description: The range of bytes to copy from the source object. The range value must use the form bytes=first-last, where the first and last are the zero-based byte offsets to copy. For example, bytes=0-9 indicates that you want to copy the first ten bytes of the source. You can copy a range only if the source object is greater than 5 MB.

Flags.Name: region
Flags.Description: The `REGION` where the bucket is present. If this flag is not provided, the program will use the default option specified in config.

Flags.Name: output
Flags.Description: Output `FORMAT` can be only json or text.

Flags.Name: json
Flags.Description: [Deprecated] Output returned in raw JSON format.

Commands.Name: create
Commands.Description: Create an application.
Commands.Usage: create --name APP_NAME ((--image IMAGE_REF | (--build-source SOURCE [--image IMAGE_REF])) [options...]

Flags.Name: name
Flags.Description: Required. The name of the application. Use a name that is unique within the project.

Flags.Name: argument
Flags.Description: Set arguments for the application. This option can be specified multiple times.

Flags.Name: cluster-local
Flags.Description: Deploy the application with a project-only endpoint. Setting a project-only endpoint means that your app is not accessible from the public internet and network access is only possible from other Code Engine components that are running in the same project.

Flags.Name: command
Flags.Description: Set commands for the application. This option can be specified multiple times.

Flags.Name: concurrency
Flags.Description: The maximum number of requests that can be processed concurrently per instance.

Flags.Name: concurrency-target
Flags.Description: The threshold of concurrent requests per instance at which one or more additional instances are created. Use this value to scale up instances based on concurrent number of requests. This option defaults to the value of the 'concurrency' option, if not specified.

Flags.Name: cpu
Flags.Description: The amount of CPU set for the instance of the application. For valid values see https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/codeengine?topic=codeengine-mem-cpu-combo.

Flags.Name: env
Flags.Description: Set environment variables in the application. Must be in NAME=VALUE format. This option can be specified multiple times.

Flags.Name: env-from-configmap
Flags.Description: Set environment variables from the key-value pairs that are stored in this configmap. Provide NAME to reference the full configmap, or PREFIX=NAME to reference the full configmap where each key is prefixed with PREFIX, or NAME:KEY_A,KEY_B to reference individual keys. To specify a new name for a referenced key, use format NAME:NEW_KEY_NAME=KEY_A. This option can be specified multiple times.

Flags.Name: env-from-secret
Flags.Description: Set environment variables from the key-value pairs that are stored in this secret. Provide NAME to reference the full secret, or PREFIX=NAME to reference the full secret where each key is prefixed with PREFIX, or NAME:KEY_A,KEY_B to reference individual keys. To specify a new name for a referenced key, use format NAME:NEW_KEY_NAME=KEY_A. This option can be specified multiple times.

Flags.Name: ephemeral-storage
Flags.Description: The amount of ephemeral storage to set for the instance of the application. Use 'M' for megabytes or 'G' for gigabytes.

Flags.Name: force
Flags.Description: Do not verify the existence of specified configmap and secret references.

Flags.Name: image
Flags.Description: The name of the image that is used for this application. The format is 'REGISTRY/NAMESPACE/REPOSITORY:TAG' where 'REGISTRY' and 'TAG' are optional. If 'REGISTRY' is not specified, the default is 'docker.io'. If 'TAG' is not specified, the default is 'latest'. The image option is required if the 'build-source' option is not specified.

Flags.Name: max-scale
Flags.Description: The maximum number of instances that can be used for this application. If you set this value to '0', the application scales as needed. The application scaling is limited only by the instances per the resource quota for the project of your application. See https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/codeengine?topic=codeengine-limits.

Flags.Name: memory
Flags.Description: The amount of memory set for the instance of the application. Use 'M' for megabytes or 'G' for gigabytes. For valid values see https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/codeengine?topic=codeengine-mem-cpu-combo.

Flags.Name: min-scale
Flags.Description: The minimum number of instances that can be used for this application.

Flags.Name: mount-configmap
Flags.Description: Mount a configmap. The format is MOUNT_DIRECTORY=CONFIGMAP_NAME. This option can be specified multiple times.

Flags.Name: mount-secret
Flags.Description: Mount a secret. The format is MOUNT_DIRECTORY=SECRET_NAME. This option can be specified multiple times.

Flags.Name: no-cluster-local
Flags.Description: Deploy the application with a public endpoint. The application deploys such that it can receive requests from the public internet or from components within the Code Engine project.

Flags.Name: no-wait
Flags.Description: Create the application and do not wait for the application to be ready.

Flags.Name: output
Flags.Description: Output format. Valid values are 'json', 'yaml', 'jsonpath=JSONPATH_EXPRESSION', 'jsonpath-as-json=JSONPATH_EXPRESSION', 'url', and 'project-url'.

Flags.Name: port
Flags.Description: The port where the application listens. The format is NAME:PORT, where NAME is optional. If NAME is specified, valid values are 'h2c', or 'http1'. When NAME is not specified or is 'http1', the port uses HTTP 1.1. When NAME is 'h2c', the port uses unencrypted HTTP 2.

Flags.Name: probe-live
Flags.Description: Optional. Configure the liveness probe for this application in NAME=VALUE format. Valid values for NAME are: 'type', 'port', 'path', 'interval', 'initial-delay', 'timeout', and 'failure-threshold'. This option can be specified multiple times. You must specify the 'type' property for this option. For more information about working with probes, see Configuring probes for your app https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/codeengine?topic=codeengine-app-probes

Flags.Name: probe-ready
Flags.Description: Optional. Configure the readiness probe for this application in NAME=VALUE format. Valid values for NAME are: 'type', 'port', 'path', 'interval', 'initial-delay', 'timeout', and 'failure-threshold'. This option can be specified multiple times. You must specify the 'type' property for this option. For more information about working with probes, see Configuring probes for your app https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/codeengine?topic=codeengine-app-probes

Flags.Name: registry-secret
Flags.Description: The name of the registry secret. The registry secret is used to authenticate with a private registry when you download the container image. Run 'ibmcloud ce registry create' to create a registry secret.

Flags.Name: request-timeout
Flags.Description: The amount of time in seconds that is allowed for a running application to respond to a request.

Flags.Name: revision-name
Flags.Description: The name of the revision.

Flags.Name: scale-down-delay
Flags.Description: The amount of time in seconds that must pass at reduced concurrency before the application is scaled down.

Flags.Name: service-account
Flags.Description: The name of the service account. For built-in service accounts, you can use the shortened names 'manager', 'none', 'reader', and 'writer'.

Flags.Name: trusted-profiles-enabled
Flags.Description: Enable mounting of a compute resource token to the container of this application.

Flags.Name: user
Flags.Description: The user ID (UID) to run the application (e.g., 1001).

Flags.Name: visibility
Flags.Description: The visibility for the application. Valid values are 'public', 'private', and 'project'. Visibility can only be 'private' if the project supports application private visibility.

Flags.Name: wait
Flags.Description: Create the application and wait for the application to be ready.

Flags.Name: wait-timeout
Flags.Description: The length of time in seconds to wait for the application to be ready. Ignored if 'no-wait' is set.

Flags.Name: build-commit
Flags.Description: The commit, tag, or branch in the source repository to pull.

Flags.Name: build-context-dir
Flags.Description: The directory in the repository that contains the buildpacks file or the Dockerfile.

Flags.Name: build-dockerfile
Flags.Description: The path to the Dockerfile.

Flags.Name: build-git-repo-secret
Flags.Description: The name of the SSH secret, which contains the credentials to access the private repository that contains the source code to build your container image.

Flags.Name: build-size
Flags.Description: The size to use for the build, which determines the amount of resources used. Valid values include small, medium, large, xlarge, and xxlarge. For details, see https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/codeengine?topic=codeengine-plan-build#build-size.

Flags.Name: build-source
Flags.Description: The URL of the Git repository or the path to local source.

Flags.Name: build-strategy
Flags.Description: The strategy to use for building the image. Valid values are 'dockerfile' and 'buildpacks'.

Flags.Name: build-timeout
Flags.Description: The amount of time, in seconds, that can pass before the build must succeed or fail.

Flags.Name: command
Flags.Description: Set commands for runs of the job. This option can be specified multiple times.

Flags.Name: cpu
Flags.Description: The amount of CPU to set for runs of the job. For valid values see https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/codeengine?topic=codeengine-mem-cpu-combo.

Flags.Name: env
Flags.Description: Set environment variables for runs of the job. Must be in NAME=VALUE format. This option can be specified multiple times.

Flags.Description: Do not verify the existence of specified configmap and secret references.

Flags.Description: The maximum execution time in seconds for runs of the job. This option can only be specified if 'mode' is 'task'.

Flags.Name: retrylimit
Flags.Description: The number of times to rerun an instance of this job run before the job run is marked as failed. This option can only be specified if 'mode' is 'task'.

Flags.Name: service-account
Flags.Description: The name of the service account. For built-in service accounts, you can use the shortened names 'manager', 'none', 'reader', and 'writer'. This cannot be specified if 'job' option is specified.

Flags.Name: wait
Flags.Description: Submit the job run and wait for the instances of this job run to complete.

Flags.Name: wait-timeout
Flags.Description: The length of time in seconds to wait for the instances of this job run to complete. Ignored if 'no-wait' is set.

Flags.Description: Required. The name of the job run.

Flags.Description: Output format. Valid values are 'json', 'yaml', 'jsonpath=JSONPATH_EXPRESSION', and 'jsonpath-as-json=JSONPATH_EXPRESSION'.

Commands.Name: resubmit
Commands.Description: Resubmit a job run based on the configuration of a previous job run.
Commands.Usage: resubmit --jobrun REFERENCED_JOBRUN_NAME [options...]

Flags.Name: jobrun
Flags.Description: Required. The name of the previous job run that this job run is based on.

Flags.Name: argument
Flags.Description: Set arguments for this job run. This option can be specified multiple times.

Flags.Name: arguments-clear
Flags.Description: Clear job run arguments.

Flags.Name: array-indices
Flags.Description: Specifies the indices of the instances that are used for this job run, e.g. '0,3,6,9', '1-5,7-8,10'. The result set of indices is limited to 1000 entries. This option can only be specified if 'array-size' is not specified.

Flags.Name: array-size
Flags.Description: Specifies the number of instances that are used for this job run. When you use this option, the system converts to array indices. For example, if you specify 'array-size' of 5, the system converts to 'array-indices' of '0 - 4'. This option can only be specified if 'array-indices' is not specified.

Flags.Name: array-size-var-override
Flags.Description: Specifies a custom value for the 'JOB_ARRAY_SIZE' environment variable. By default, the 'JOB_ARRAY_SIZE' environment variable is set to either the 'array-size' value or the number of indices specified by 'array-indices'.

Flags.Name: command
Flags.Description: Set commands for this job run. This option can be specified multiple times.

Flags.Name: commands-clear
Flags.Description: Clear job run commands.

Flags.Name: cpu
Flags.Description: The amount of CPU set for each array index for this job run. For valid values see https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/codeengine?topic=codeengine-mem-cpu-combo.

Flags.Name: env
Flags.Description: Set environment variables for this job run. Must be in NAME=VALUE format. This option can be specified multiple times.

Flags.Name: env-from-configmap
Flags.Description: Set environment variables from the key-value pairs that are stored in this configmap. Provide NAME to reference the full configmap, or PREFIX=NAME to reference the full configmap where each key is prefixed with PREFIX, or NAME:KEY_A,KEY_B to reference individual keys. To specify a new name for a referenced key, use format NAME:NEW_KEY_NAME=KEY_A. This option can be specified multiple times.

Flags.Name: env-from-configmap-rm
Flags.Description: Remove environment variable references to full configmaps by using the configmap name. This option can be specified multiple times.

Flags.Name: env-from-secret
Flags.Description: Set environment variables from the key-value pairs that are stored in this secret. Provide NAME to reference the full secret, or PREFIX=NAME to reference the full secret where each key is prefixed with PREFIX, or NAME:KEY_A,KEY_B to reference individual keys. To specify a new name for a referenced key, use format NAME:NEW_KEY_NAME=KEY_A. This option can be specified multiple times.

Flags.Name: env-from-secret-rm
Flags.Description: Remove environment variable references to full secrets by using the secret name. This option can be specified multiple times.

Flags.Name: env-rm
Flags.Description: Remove environment variables by using their KEY. This option can be specified multiple times.

Flags.Name: ephemeral-storage
Flags.Description: The amount of ephemeral storage for this job run. Use 'M' for megabytes or 'G' for gigabytes.

Flags.Name: force
Flags.Description: Do not verify the existence of specified configmap and secret references.

Flags.Name: maxexecutiontime
Flags.Description: The maximum execution time in seconds for this job run. This option can only be specified if 'mode' is 'task'.

Flags.Name: memory
Flags.Description: The amount of memory to assign to this job run. Use 'M' for megabytes or 'G' for gigabytes. For valid values see https://cloud.ibm.com/docs/codeengine?topic=codeengine-mem-cpu-combo.

Flags.Name: mode
Flags.Description: The mode of the job run. Valid values are 'task' and 'daemon'. In 'task' mode, the 'maxexecutiontime' and 'retrylimit' options apply. In 'daemon' mode, since there is no timeout and failed instances are restarted indefinitely, the 'maxexecutiontime' and 'retrylimit' options are not allowed.

Flags.Name: mount-configmap
Flags.Description: Mount a configmap. The format is MOUNT_DIRECTORY=CONFIGMAP_NAME. This option can be specified multiple times.

Flags.Name: mount-rm
Flags.Description: Remove a mounted volume by using its mount directory. This option can be specified multiple times.

Flags.Name: mount-secret
Flags.Description: Mount a secret. The format is MOUNT_DIRECTORY=SECRET_NAME. This option can be specified multiple times.

Flags.Name: name
Flags.Description: The name of this job run. Required if the referenced job run does not have a related job.

Flags.Name: no-wait
Flags.Description: Resubmit the job run and do not wait for the instances of this job run to complete.

Flags.Name: output
Flags.Description: Output format. Valid values are 'json', 'yaml', 'jsonpath=JSONPATH_EXPRESSION', and 'jsonpath-as-json=JSONPATH_EXPRESSION'.

Flags.Name: retrylimit
Flags.Description: The number of times to rerun an instance of this job run before the job run is marked as failed. This option can only be specified if 'mode' is 'task'.

Flags.Name: service-account
Flags.Description: The name of the service account. For built-in service accounts, you can use the shortened names 'manager', 'none', 'reader', and 'writer'. This cannot be specified if referenced job run has a related job.

Flags.Name: service-account-clear
Flags.Description: Clear the service account.

Flags.Name: wait
Flags.Description: Resubmit the job run and wait for the instances of this job run to complete.

Flags.Name: wait-timeout
Flags.Description: The length of time in seconds to wait for the instances of this job run to complete. Ignored if 'no-wait' is set.

Commands.Name: namespace-add
Commands.Description: Add a namespace to your account. You must set at least one namespace to store images in IBM Cloud Container Registry.
Commands.Usage:
ibmcloud cr namespace-add [-g (RESOURCE_GROUP_NAME | RESOURCE_GROUP_ID)] NAMESPACE
NAMESPACE is the name of the namespace to add. Do not put personal information in your namespace name.

Flags.Name: g
Flags.Description: Optional: Specify the name or ID of the resource group to which you want to assign the namespace.

Commands.Name: namespace-assign
Commands.Description: Assign a currently unassigned namespace to the targeted resource group.
Commands.Usage:
ibmcloud cr namespace-assign [-g (RESOURCE_GROUP_NAME | RESOURCE_GROUP_ID)] NAMESPACE
NAMESPACE is the name of the namespace that you want to assign to the targeted resource group.

Flags.Name: g
Flags.Description: Optional: Specify the name or ID of the resource group to which you want to assign the namespace.

Commands.Name: namespace-rm
Commands.Description: Delete a namespace from your account, and also delete all images within that namespace.

ibmcloud cr namespace-rm NAMESPACE [--force | -f]
NAMESPACE is the name of the namespace to delete.

Flags.Name: force, f
Flags.Description: Optional: Force the command to run with no user prompts.

ibmcloud cr image-inspect [--format FORMAT] IMAGE [IMAGE...]
IMAGE is the name of an image to inspect.
IMAGE must be in the format <REPOSITORY>:<TAG>, or <REPOSITORY>@<DIGEST>, for example: us.icr.io/namespace/image:latest

Flags.Name: format
Flags.Description: Optional: Formats the command output by using the specified Go template.

Commands.Name: manifest-inspect
Commands.Description: Inspect an image manifest in IBM Cloud Container Registry.
Commands.Usage:
ibmcloud cr manifest-inspect [--quiet] IMAGE
IMAGE is the name of the image for which you want to inspect the manifest.
IMAGE must be in the format <REPOSITORY>:<TAG>, or <REPOSITORY>@<DIGEST>, for example: us.icr.io/namespace/image:latest

Flags.Name: quiet, q
Flags.Description: Optional: Reduces the output to display essential elements only.

Commands.Name: image-tag
Commands.Description: Create a new tag, TARGET_IMAGE, that refers to a source image, SOURCE_IMAGE, in IBM Cloud Container Registry.
Commands.Usage:
ibmcloud cr image-tag [SOURCE_IMAGE] [TARGET_IMAGE]
SOURCE_IMAGE is the name of an image to add a new tag to.
TARGET_IMAGE is the new tag for the image.
SOURCE_IMAGE must be in the format <REPOSITORY>:<TAG>, or <REPOSITORY>@<DIGEST>
TARGET_IMAGE must be in the format <REPOSITORY>:<TAG>, for example: us.icr.io/namespace/image:latest
SOURCE_IMAGE and TARGET_IMAGE must both be in the same region as the one you are logged into.

Commands.Name: image-untag
Commands.Description: Remove tags from one or more images in IBM Cloud Container Registry.
Commands.Usage:
ibmcloud cr image-untag IMAGE [IMAGE...]
IMAGE must be in the format <REPOSITORY>:<TAG> for example: us.icr.io/namespace/image:latest
Where <TAG> is the tag that you want to delete.

Commands.Name: login
Commands.Description: Log the local Docker or Podman client in to IBM Cloud Container Registry.
Commands.Usage: ibmcloud cr login [--client CLIENT]

Flags.Name: client
Flags.Description: Optional: Selects the CLIENT to log in. Use 'docker' or 'podman'. The default is 'docker' if Docker is installed or 'podman' if Docker is not installed.

Commands.Name: vulnerability-assessment
Commands.Description: Display detailed vulnerability assessment reports for one or more images in IBM Cloud Container Registry.
Commands.Usage:
ibmcloud cr vulnerability-assessment IMAGE [IMAGE...] [--extended | -e] [--vulnerabilities | -v] [--configuration-issues | -c] [--output FORMAT | -o FORMAT]
IMAGE is the name of an image in IBM Cloud Container Registry.
To find the names of your images, run 'ibmcloud cr image-list' and combine the values of the REPOSITORY and TAG columns in the following format: <REPOSITORY>:<TAG> for example: us.icr.io/namespace/image:latest

Flags.Name: output,o
Flags.Description: Optional: The command output is returned in the chosen format (supported formats: 'text', 'json').

Flags.Name: vulnerabilities, v
Flags.Description: Optional: The command output is restricted to show vulnerabilities only.

Flags.Name: configuration-issues, c
Flags.Description: Optional: The command output is restricted to show configuration issues only.

Flags.Name: extended, e
Flags.Description: Optional: The command output shows additional fix information for vulnerable packages.

Commands.Name: exemption-list
Commands.Description: List your exemptions for security issues.
Commands.Usage: ibmcloud cr exemption-list [--scope SCOPE] [--output | -o [json]]

Flags.Name: scope
Flags.Description: To set your account as the scope, use "*" as the value. To set a namespace, repository, tag, or digest as the scope, enter the value in one of the following formats: namespace, namespace/repository, namespace/repository:tag, namespace/repository@sha256:hash

Flags.Name: output, o
Flags.Description: Optional: The command output is returned in the chosen format (supported formats: 'json').

Commands.Name: exemption-add
Commands.Description: Create an exemption for a security issue. You can create an exemption for a security issue that applies to different scopes. The scope can be the account, namespace, repository, tag, or digest.
Commands.Usage: ibmcloud cr exemption-add --scope SCOPE --issue-type ISSUE_TYPE --issue-id ISSUE_ID [--output | -o [json]]

Flags.Name: scope
Flags.Description: To set your account as the scope, use "*" as the value. To set a namespace, repository, tag, or digest as the scope, enter the value in one of the following formats: namespace, namespace/repository, namespace/repository:tag, namespace/repository@sha256:hash

Flags.Name: issue-type
Flags.Description: The type of security issue that you want to exempt. To find valid issue types, run 'ibmcloud cr exemption-types'.

Flags.Name: issue-id
Flags.Description: The ID of the security issue that you want to exempt. To find an issue ID, run 'ibmcloud cr va <image>'', where <image> is the name of your image, and use the relevant value from either the Vulnerability ID or Configuration Issue ID column.

Flags.Name: output, o
Flags.Description: Optional: The command output is returned in the chosen format (supported formats: 'json').

Commands.Name: exemption-rm
Commands.Description: Delete an exemption for a security issue. To view your existing exemptions, run 'ibmcloud cr exemption-list'.
Commands.Usage: ibmcloud cr exemption-rm --scope SCOPE --issue-type ISSUE_TYPE --issue-id ISSUE_ID [--output | -o [json]]

Flags.Name: scope
Flags.Description: To set your account as the scope, use "*" as the value. To set a namespace, repository, tag, or digest as the scope, enter the value in one of the following formats: namespace, namespace/repository, namespace/repository:tag, namespace/repository@sha256:hash

Flags.Name: issue-type
Flags.Description: The issue type of the exemption for the security issue that you want to remove. To find the issue types for your exemptions, run 'ibmcloud cr exemption-list'.

Flags.Name: issue-id
Flags.Description: The ID of the exemption for the security issue that you want to remove. To find the issue IDs for your exemptions, run 'ibmcloud cr exemption-list'.

Commands.Name: exemption-types
Commands.Description: Lists the types of security issues that you can exempt.
Commands.Usage: ibmcloud cr exemption-types [--output | -o [json]]

Flags.Name: output, o
Flags.Description: Optional: The command output is returned in the chosen format (supported formats: 'json').

Commands.Name: retention-run
Commands.Description: Retains a specified number of images for each repository within a namespace in IBM Cloud Container Registry. All other images in the namespace are deleted.
Commands.Usage:
ibmcloud cr retention-run [--force | -f ] [--output | -o [json]] [--retain-untagged] --images IMAGECOUNT NAMESPACE
NAMESPACE is the namespace that you want to delete images from.

Flags.Name: force, f
Flags.Description: Optional: Force the command to run with no user prompts.

Flags.Name: images
Flags.Description: Determines how many images to keep within each repository in the specified namespace. The newest images are retained. Age of images is determined by their build date.

Flags.Name: retain-untagged
Flags.Description: Optional: Retain all untagged images when the retention policy is being processed. If the option isn't specified, all tagged and untagged images are analyzed

Flags.Name: output, o
Flags.Description: Optional: The command output is returned in the chosen format (supported formats: 'json').

Flags.Name: json
Flags.Description: Optional: Outputs the list in JSON format.

Commands.Name: image-restore
Commands.Description: Restores an image from the trash.
Commands.Usage:
ibmcloud cr image-restore IMAGE
IMAGE is the name of the image to restore.
To restore a tag, IMAGE must be in the format <REPOSITORY>:<TAG>, for example: us.icr.io/namespace/image:latest
To restore all tags for a digest in a repository, IMAGE must be in the format <REPOSITORY>@<DIGEST>, for example: us.icr.io/namespace/image@sha256:c909842be4f69ce8478ecb05dfe0f77fdec623d644eba6f5a2c937b7075b3962

Commands.Name: retention-policy-set
Commands.Description: Set a scheduled policy to retain a specified number of images for each repository within a namespace in IBM Cloud Container Registry. Policy will run immediately. All other images in the namespace are deleted.
Commands.Usage:
ibmcloud cr retention-policy-set [--retain-untagged] [--force | -f] --images IMAGECOUNT NAMESPACE
NAMESPACE is the namespace for which you want to create a policy.

Flags.Name: images
Flags.Description: Determines how many images to keep within each repository in the specified namespace. To keep all images use 'All'. The newest images are retained. Age of images is determined by their build date.

Flags.Name: retain-untagged
Flags.Description: Optional: Retain all untagged images when the retention policy is being processed. If the option isn't specified, all tagged and untagged images are analyzed

Flags.Name: force, f
Flags.Description: Optional: Force the command to run with no user prompts.

Commands.Name: retention-policy-list

Commands.Usage: ibmcloud cr retention-policy-list [--output | -o [json]]

Flags.Name: output, o
Flags.Description: Optional: The command output is returned in the chosen format (supported formats: 'json').

Flags.Name: restrict
Flags.Description: Optional: Restricts the command output to a specified namespace.

Flags.Name: output, o
Flags.Description: Optional: The command output is returned in the chosen format (supported formats: 'json').

Flags.Name: json
Flags.Description: Optional: Outputs the list in JSON format.

Commands.Name: update
Commands.Description: Update a log forwarding configuration for a cluster.
Commands.Usage: ibmcloud ks logging config update --cluster CLUSTER --id ID --logsource LOGSOURCE --type TYPE [--force-update] [--hostname HOSTNAME] [--output OUTPUT] [--port PORT] [-q] (--ca-cert CERT --syslog-protocol PROTOCOL --verify-mode MODE | --org ORG --skip-validation --space SPACE) (--namespace NAMESPACE | -C CONTAINER -p PATH)

Flags.Name: cluster, c
Flags.Description: Specify the cluster name or ID.

Flags.Name: id
Flags.Description: Specify the ID of the logging configuration.

Flags.Name: namespace, n
Flags.Description: The namespace you want to apply the log forwarding configuration to. Only use this flag with the 'container' log source or if you do not specify a log source. If you do not specify a namespace, then all namespaces use this configuration.

Flags.Name: logsource
Flags.Description: The source of the logs to forward. Supported values are 'container', 'application', 'ingress', 'worker', 'storage', and 'kubernetes'. This argument supports a comma separated list of log sources. If you do not provide a log source, logs for 'container' and 'ingress' are forwarded.

Flags.Name: type
Flags.Description: The log forwarding protocol that you want to use. The only supported value is 'syslog'.

Flags.Name: syslog-protocol
Flags.Description: When the logging type is 'syslog', the transport layer protocol. Supported values are 'tls', 'tcp' and the default 'udp'. When forwarding to an rsyslog server with the UDP protocol, logs that are over 1KB are truncated.

Flags.Name: ca-cert
Flags.Description: When the logging type is 'syslog' and the protocol is tls, the Kubernetes secret name that contains the Certificate Authority certificate.

Flags.Name: verify-mode
Flags.Description: When the logging type is 'syslog' and the protocol is tls, the verification mode. Supported values are 'verify-peer' and the default 'verify-none'.

Flags.Name: hostname
Flags.Description: When logging type is 'syslog', the hostname or IP address of the log collector. When logging type is 'ibm' (deprecated), the logging ingest endpoint. If you do not provide the logging ingest endpoint, then the current region's endpoint is used.

Flags.Name: port
Flags.Description: The port of the log collector. If you do not specify a port, the default port for the ingestion endpoint is used for 'ibm' (deprecated) and '514' is used for 'syslog'.

Flags.Name: org
Flags.Description: ::deprecated::The org name to send logs to. This flag is only valid when the logging type is 'ibm'. The org name is required when you specify a space name. If you do not specify a space name, then logs are forwarded at the account level.

Flags.Name: space
Flags.Description: ::deprecated::The space name to send logs to. This flag is only valid when the logging type is 'ibm'. The space name is required when you specify an org name. If you do not specify a space name, then logs are forwarded at the account level.

Flags.Name: skip-validation
Flags.Description: Skips validation of the org and space names when they are specified. This can result in a broken logging config if the values are invalid but will take less time to process.

Flags.Name: app-containers
Flags.Description: Specify the containers that you want to collect logs for. To specify more than one path, use multiple flags, such as '-C container1 -C container2'. This option is required for the 'application' log source. If not provided, logs are collected from all containers from the application log paths passed in.

Flags.Name: C, app-container
Flags.Description: Specify the containers that you want to collect logs for. To specify more than one path, use multiple flags, such as '-C container1 -C container2'. This option is required for the 'application' log source. If not provided, logs are collected from all containers from the application log paths passed in.

Flags.Name: app-paths
Flags.Description: Specify the absolute file path to collect logs from inside the container. To specify more than one path, use multiple flags, such as `-p path1 -p path2`. Required parameter when specifying 'application' for the log source. Wildcards such as '/var/log/*.log' are accepted but recursive globs such are '/var/log/**/test.log' are not.

Flags.Name: p, app-path
Flags.Description: Specify the absolute file path to collect logs from inside the container. To specify more than one path, use multiple flags, such as `-p path1 -p path2`. Required parameter when specifying 'application' for the log source. Wildcards such as '/var/log/*.log' are accepted but recursive globs such are '/var/log/**/test.log' are not.

Commands.Name: create
Commands.Description: Filter out logs that are forwarded by your logging configuration.
Commands.Usage: ibmcloud ks logging filter create --cluster CLUSTER [--container CONTAINER] [--force-update] [--lc LOGGING-CONFIG ...] [--level LEVEL] [--namespace NAMESPACE] [--output OUTPUT] [-q] [--type TYPE] (--message MESSAGE | --regex-message MESSAGE)

Flags.Name: cluster, c
Flags.Description: Specify the cluster name or ID.

Flags.Name: type
Flags.Description: The type of logs that you want to apply the filter to. Currently all, container, and host are supported.

Flags.Name: logging-configs
Flags.Description: A comma separated list of your logging configuration IDs. If not provided, the filter is applied to all the cluster logging configurations that are passed to the filter. You can view log configurations that match the filter by using the --show-matching-configs flag with the command.

Flags.Name: namespace, n
Flags.Description: The Kubernetes namespace from which you want to filter logs.

Flags.Name: container
Flags.Description: The name of the container from which you want to filter out logs. This flag applies only when you are using log type container.

Flags.Name: level
Flags.Description: Filters out logs that are at the specified level and less. Acceptable values in their canonical order are fatal, error, warn/warning, info, debug, and trace. As an example, if you filtered logs at the info level, debug, and trace are also filtered. **Note**: You can use this flag only when log messages are in JSON format and contain a level field. Example output: {"log": "hello", "level": "info"}

Flags.Name: message
Flags.Description: Filters out any logs that contain a specified message anywhere in the log. The message is matched literally and not as an expression. Example: The messages "Hello", "!", and "Hello, World!", would apply to the log "Hello, World!".

Flags.Name: regex-message
Flags.Description: Filters out any logs that contain a specified message regex pattern in the log. The message is matched as a regular expression. Example: The pattern "hello [0-9]" would apply to "hello 1", "hello 2", "hello 9"

Commands.Name: classic
Commands.Description: Enable or disable an Ingress ALB in a classic cluster.
Commands.Usage: ibmcloud ks alb configure classic --alb-id ID [-q] [--user-ip IP] [--version VERSION] (--disable | --disable-deployment | --enable)

Flags.Name: alb-id
Flags.Description: The ALB ID. To see available ALB IDs, run 'ibmcloud ks alb ls'.

Flags.Name: enable
Flags.Description: Enable an ALB for the cluster. Must include either '--enable', '--disable', or '--disable-deployment' in the command, but must not include more than one flag.

Flags.Name: disable
Flags.Description: Disable an ALB for the cluster. Must include either '--enable', '--disable', or '--disable-deployment' in the command, but must not include more than one flag.

Flags.Name: disable-deployment
Flags.Description: Disable the ALB deployment only. If provided, the ALB deployment is deleted but the IBM-provided Ingress subdomain remains. Must include either '--enable', '--disable', or '--disable-deployment' in the command, but must not include more than one flag.

Flags.Name: user-ip
Flags.Description: Specify a portable public or private IP address that is available on the 'vlan' and in the 'zone' of the ALB to be created or configured.

Flags.Name: version
Flags.Description: [Beta] Specify the ALB image version. To see supported image versions, run 'ibmcloud ks alb versions'.

Flags.Name: q
Flags.Description: Do not show the message of the day or update reminders.

Commands.Name: classic
Commands.Description: Create a cluster with worker nodes on classic infrastructure.

Flags.Name: name
Flags.Description: Enter a name for the cluster.

Flags.Name: zone
Flags.Description: Specify the zone for the worker pool in a multizone cluster. To list available zones, run 'ibmcloud ks zone ls'.

Flags.Name: private-vlan
Flags.Description: Conditional: Specify the ID of the private VLAN. To see available VLANs, run 'ibmcloud ks vlan ls --zone <zone name>'. If you do not have a private VLAN yet, do not specify this option because one will be automatically created for you. When you specify a private VLAN, you must also specify either the '--public-vlan' flag or the '--private-only' flag.

Flags.Name: public-vlan
Flags.Description: Conditional: Specify the ID of the public VLAN. To see available VLANs, run 'ibmcloud ks vlan ls --zone <zone name>'. If you do not have a public VLAN yet, do not specify this option because one will be automatically created for you.

Flags.Name: private-only
Flags.Description: Use this flag to prevent a public VLAN from being created. Required only when you specify the '--private-vlan' flag without specifying the '--public-vlan' flag.

Flags.Name: operating-system
Flags.Description: Specify the name of the operating system.

Flags.Name: workers
Flags.Description: The number of cluster worker nodes. Defaults to 1.

Flags.Name: hardware
Flags.Description: The level of hardware isolation for your worker node. Use 'dedicated' to have available physical resources dedicated to you only, or 'shared' to allow physical resources to be shared with other IBM customers. For IBM Cloud Public accounts, the default value is shared. For IBM Cloud Dedicated accounts, dedicated is the only available option.

Flags.Name: no-subnet
Flags.Description: Prevent the creation of a portable subnet when creating the cluster. By default, both a public and a private portable subnet are created on the associated VLAN, and this flag prevents that behavior. To add a subnet to the cluster later, run 'ibmcloud ks cluster subnet add'.

Flags.Name: pod-subnet
Flags.Description: Specify a custom subnet CIDR to provide private IP addresses for pods. The subnet must be at least '/23' or larger. For more info, see 'https://ibm.biz/cluster-create-classic'

Flags.Name: service-subnet
Flags.Description: Specify a custom subnet CIDR to provide private IP addresses for services. The subnet must be at least '/24' or larger. For more info, see 'https://ibm.biz/cluster-create-classic'. Default value: '172.21.0.0/16'

Flags.Name: disable-disk-encrypt
Flags.Description: Disable encryption on a worker node.

Flags.Name: entitlement
Flags.Description: Set this flag to 'ocp_entitled' only if you use this cluster with a license such as a Cloud Pak that has an OpenShift entitlement.

Flags.Name: file
Flags.Description: Provide a file that contains input parameters in YAML format.

Flags.Name: location
Flags.Description: ::deprecated::Flag maintained for compatibility with an earlier version. Use the '--zone' flag instead.

Flags.Name: private-service-endpoint
Flags.Description: Enable the private service endpoint to make the master privately accessible.

Flags.Name: private-service-endpoint-allowlist
Flags.Description: ::deprecated::Enable access control to a cluster master via a private service endpoint allowlist. For more info, see 'https://ibm.biz/se_allowlist'.

Flags.Name: skip-advance-permissions-check
Flags.Description: Skip checking for infrastructure permissions before completing this action. Note that if you do not have the correct infrastructure permissions, this action might only partially succeed.

Flags.Name: sm-instance
Flags.Description: The CRN of the IBM Cloud Secrets Manager instance.

Flags.Name: sm-group
Flags.Description: The Secret Group ID of the IBM Cloud Secrets Manager instance where your secrets are persisted.

Flags.Name: machine-type
Flags.Description: The flavor of the worker node. To see available flavors, run 'ibmcloud ks machine-types --zone <zone name>' (for public IBM Cloud accounts) or 'ibmcloud ks machine-types' (for IBM Cloud Dedicated accounts).

Flags.Description: Specify the Kubernetes version, including at least the major.minor version. If you do not include this flag, the default version is used. To see available versions, run 'ibmcloud ks versions'.

Commands.Usage: ibmcloud ks cluster service bind --cluster CLUSTER --namespace NAMESPACE --service SERVICE [-q] (--key KEY | --role ROLE)

Flags.Name: cluster, c
Flags.Description: Specify the cluster name or ID.

Flags.Name: namespace, n
Flags.Description: Specify the Kubernetes namespace.

Flags.Name: key
Flags.Description: Specify the name or GUID of an existing service key. If you define a service key, you cannot set the '--role' option at the same time.

Flags.Name: role
Flags.Description: Specify the IAM role for the service key. This flag does not work if you specify an existing key to use or for services that are not IAM-enabled, such as Cloud Foundry services.

Flags.Name: service
Flags.Description: Specify the name of the service instance. To see a list of available service instances, run 'ibmcloud service list' for Cloud Foundry services, or 'ibmcloud resource service-instances' for IAM-enabled services.

Flags.Name: q
Flags.Description: Do not show the message of the day or update reminders.

Flags.Name: s
Flags.Description: Do not show the message of the day or update reminders.

Flags.Description: Specify the cluster name or ID.

Flags.Name: name
Flags.Description: A name for the Ingress secret that is created in the cluster.

Flags.Name: namespace, n
Flags.Description: Specify the Kubernetes namespace.

Flags.Name: cert-crn
Flags.Description: The certificate CRN.

Flags.Name: field
Flags.Description: The secret CRN to include as a field. To pull in the secret without specifying the name, use '--field <crn>'. To specify the field name, use '--field name=<crn>'. To use the IBM Cloud Secrets Manager secret as the prefix, use '--field prefix=<crn>'.

Flags.Name: type
Flags.Description: The Ingress secret type. Can be TLS or Opaque. If no option is specified, TLS is applied by default.

Flags.Name: persist
Flags.Description: Persist the secret in the cluster so that it cannot be deleted.

Commands.Name: clean
Commands.Description: Clean up any resources and ConfigMaps that you no longer need, such as after an Ingress migration.
Commands.Usage: ibmcloud ks ingress alb migrate clean --cluster CLUSTER [-f] [--generated-resources] [--iks-ingresses] [--kube-ingresses] [--output OUTPUT] [-q] [--reset-kube-controller-configmap] [--test-ingresses]

Flags.Name: cluster, c
Flags.Description: Specify the cluster name or ID.

Commands.Name: configure
Commands.Description: Configure a health check monitor for an existing NLB host name in a cluster. To enable the monitor, include the '--enable' flag. To update an existing monitor, include only the flags for the settings that you want to change.
Commands.Usage: ibmcloud ks nlb-dns monitor configure --cluster CLUSTER --nlb-host HOST [--allows-insecure] [--description DESCRIPTION] [--enable] [--expected-body BODY] [--expected-codes CODES] [--follows-redirects] [--header HEADER ...] [--interval INTERVAL] [--method METHOD] [--output OUTPUT] [--path PATH] [--port PORT] [-q] [--retries RETRIES] [--timeout TIMEOUT] [--type TYPE]

Flags.Name: cluster, c
Flags.Description: Specify the cluster name or ID.

Flags.Name: nlb-host
Flags.Description: The host name. To see existing host names, run 'ibmcloud ks nlb-dns ls'.

Flags.Name: type
Flags.Description: The protocol to use for the health check.

Flags.Name: enable
Flags.Description: Enable the health check monitor for the host name.

Flags.Name: description
Flags.Description: Description of the health monitor.

Flags.Name: method
Flags.Description: The method to use for the health check. Default for HTTP and HTTPS: 'GET'. Default for TCP: 'connection_established'

Flags.Name: path
Flags.Description: The endpoint path to health check against. This flag is valid only for type 'HTTP' or 'HTTPS'. Default: '/'

Flags.Name: timeout
Flags.Description: The timeout, in seconds, before the IP is considered unhealthy. Must be in the range [1, 15]. Default: '5'

Flags.Name: retries
Flags.Description: When a timeout occurs, the number of retries to attempt before the IP is considered unhealthy. Retries are attempted immediately. Must be in the range [0, 5]. Default: '2'

Flags.Name: interval
Flags.Description: The interval, in seconds, between each health check. Short intervals might improve failover time but increase load on the IPs. The value must be greater than ('retries_value' + 1) * 'timeout_value', and must be in the range [10, 3600]. Default: '60'

Flags.Name: port
Flags.Description: The port number to connect to for the health check. When type is TCP, this flag is required. When type is HTTP or HTTPS, use this flag only for ports other than 80 for HTTP or 443 for HTTPS. HTTP default: '80'. HTTPS default: '443'.

Flags.Name: expected-body
Flags.Description: A case-insensitive sub-string that the health check looks for in the response body. If this string is not found, the IP is considered unhealthy. This flag is valid only for type 'HTTP' or 'HTTPS'.

Flags.Name: expected-codes
Flags.Description: HTTP codes that the health check looks for in the response. If the HTTP code is not found, the IP is considered unhealthy. This flag is valid only for type 'HTTP' or 'HTTPS'. Default: '2xx'

Flags.Name: header
Flags.Description: HTTP request headers to send in the health check, such as a Host header. The User-Agent header cannot be overridden. This flag is valid only for type 'HTTP' or 'HTTPS'. To add more than one header to the requests, specify this flag multiple times. This flag accepts values in the following format: '--header Header-Name=value'. When updating a monitor, the existing headers are replaced by the ones you specify. To delete all existing headers specify the flag with an empty value '--header ""'.

Flags.Name: follows-redirects
Flags.Description: Set to 'true' to follow any redirects that are returned by the IP. This flag is valid only for type 'HTTP' or 'HTTPS'.

Flags.Name: allows-insecure
Flags.Description: Set to 'true' to not validate the certificate. This flag is valid only for type 'HTTP' or 'HTTPS'.

Flags.Description: Prints the command output in the provided format.

Flags.Description: <invalid Value>

Commands.Name: create
Commands.Description: Create a Satellite location. A Satellite location is a representation of an environment in your infrastructure provider. After you create a location, attach hosts from separate zones of your backing infrastructure environment with the 'ibmcloud sat host attach' command.
Commands.Usage: ibmcloud sat location create --managed-from REGION --name NAME [--capability CAPABILITY ...] [--coreos-enabled] [--cos-bucket BUCKET] [--description DESCRIPTION] [--ha-zone ZONE ...] [--physical-address ADDRESS] [--pod-network-interface-selection SELECTION] [--pod-subnet SUBNET] [--provider PROVIDER] [--provider-credential CREDENTIAL] [--provider-region REGION] [-q] [--service-subnet SUBNET]

Flags.Name: pod-subnet
Flags.Description: Specify a custom subnet CIDR to provide private IP addresses for pods. This option is used only if you enable Red Hat CoreOS with the '--coreos-enabled' option. The subnet must be '/23' or larger. See 'https://ibm.biz/sat-location-create'. Default value: '172.16.0.0/16

Flags.Name: service-subnet
Flags.Description: Specify a custom subnet CIDR to provide private IP addresses for services. This option is used only if you enable Red Hat CoreOS with the '--coreos-enabled' option. The subnet must be '/24' or larger. See 'https://ibm.biz/sat-location-create'. Default value: '172.20.0.0/16'

Flags.Name: name
Flags.Description: Specify a name for the Satellite location. Location names must start with a letter, can contain letters, numbers, periods (.), and hyphen (-), and must be fewer than 36 characters. Do not reuse names, even if the other location is deleted.

Flags.Name: managed-from
Flags.Description: Select the IBM Cloud region to manage your Satellite location from. Choose a region close to your on-prem data center for better performance. See 'https://ibm.biz/sat-region'.

Flags.Name: ha-zone
Flags.Description: Specify the zone for your location. For high availability, specify 3 zones for your location as '--ha-zone ZONE1_NAME --ha-zone ZONE2_NAME --ha-zone ZONE3_NAME'. The names of the zones must match exactly the names of the corresponding zones in your infrastructure provider where you plan to create hosts.

Flags.Name: cos-bucket
Flags.Description: Specify the name of the IBM Cloud Object Storage bucket to store your Satellite location control plane data. Otherwise, a new bucket is created for you.

Flags.Name: description
Flags.Description: Enter a description for the Satellite location.

Flags.Name: logging-account-id
Flags.Description: The IBM Cloud account ID with the instance of IBM Log Analysis with LogDNA that you want to forward your Satellite logs to. This option is available only in select environments.

Flags.Name: provider
Flags.Description: Indicate the infrastructure provider to use for the Satellite location. If you include this option, you must also include the '--provider-credential' option.

Flags.Name: provider-region
Flags.Description: Specify the region in the infrastructure provider where you plan to create the hosts for the Satellite location. If you include this option, you must also include the '--provider' option.

Flags.Name: provider-credential
Flags.Description: Specify the path to a JSON file on your local machine that has the credentials of the infrastructure provider for the Satellite location. The credential format is provider-specific. See 'http://ibm.biz/sat-infra-creds'.

Flags.Name: coreos-enabled

Commands.Name: set
Commands.Description: Set authentication settings for an endpoint. There are two TLS connections in the request flow. The 'source' options refer to the TLS handshake between the source and the Connector service. The 'destination' options refer to the TLS handshake between the Connector service and your destination or target server. You can provide certificates for one or both of these connections. Unspecified settings are set to their default values.
Commands.Usage: ibmcloud sat endpoint authn set --endpoint ENDPOINT [--dest-ca-cert-file FILE] [--dest-cert-file FILE] [--dest-key-file FILE] [--dest-tls-mode MODE] [-q] [--source-ca-cert-file FILE] [--source-cert-file FILE] [--source-key-file FILE] [--source-tls-mode MODE] (--connector-id ID | --location LOCATION)

Flags.Name: location
Flags.Description: The name or ID of the Satellite location. To find the location ID or name, run 'ibmcloud sat location ls'.

Flags.Name: connector-id
Flags.Description: The ID of the Satellite connector. To find the connector ID, run 'ibmcloud sat connector ls'.

Flags.Name: endpoint
Flags.Description: Specify the name or ID of the endpoint. To list all endpoints, run 'ibmcloud sat endpoint ls'.

Flags.Name: dest-tls-mode
Flags.Description: The destination TLS mode.

Flags.Name: dest-cert-file
Flags.Description: The client certificate used to authenticate with the destination server. For example 'myCert.pem'.

Flags.Name: dest-key-file
Flags.Description: The client private key used to encrypt the client certificate. For example 'myKey.pem'.

Flags.Name: dest-ca-cert-file
Flags.Description: Trusted CA certificate or chain used to validate the destination server's certificate. For example 'myCA.pem'.

Flags.Name: source-tls-mode
Flags.Description: The source TLS mode.

Flags.Name: source-cert-file
Flags.Description: The server certificate to present to the source client. For example 'myCert.pem'.

Flags.Name: source-key-file
Flags.Description: The server private key used to encrypt the server certificate. For example 'myKey.pem'.

Flags.Name: source-ca-cert-file
Flags.Description: Trusted CA certificate or chain used to validate the source client's certificate when source-tls-mode is mutual. For example 'myCA.pem'.

Flags.Name: q
Flags.Description: Do not show the message of the day or update reminders.

Flags.Name: s
Flags.Description: Do not show the message of the day or update reminders.

Commands.Name: set
Commands.Description: [Deactivated on 2024-10-01! Use 'ibmcloud sat endpoint authn set' instead] Set authentication settings for an endpoint. There are two TLS connections in the request flow. The 'source' options refer to the TLS handshake between the source and the Connector service. The 'destination' options refer to the TLS handshake between the Connector service and your destination or target server. You can provide certificates for one or both of these connections. Unspecified settings are set to their default values.
Commands.Usage: ibmcloud sat experimental endpoint authn set --endpoint ENDPOINT [--dest-ca-cert-file FILE] [--dest-cert-file FILE] [--dest-key-file FILE] [--dest-tls-mode MODE] [-q] [--source-ca-cert-file FILE] [--source-cert-file FILE] [--source-key-file FILE] [--source-tls-mode MODE] (--connector-id ID | --location LOCATION)

Flags.Name: connector-id
Flags.Description: The ID of the Satellite connector. To find the connector ID, run 'ibmcloud sat connector ls'.

Flags.Name: endpoint
Flags.Description: Specify the name or ID of the endpoint. To list all endpoints, run 'ibmcloud sat endpoint ls'.

Flags.Name: dest-tls-mode
Flags.Description: The destination TLS mode.

Flags.Name: dest-cert-file
Flags.Description: The client certificate used to authenticate with the destination server. For example 'myCert.pem'.

Flags.Name: dest-key-file
Flags.Description: The client private key used to encrypt the client certificate. For example 'myKey.pem'.

Flags.Name: dest-ca-cert-file
Flags.Description: Trusted CA certificate or chain used to validate the destination server's certificate. For example 'myCA.pem'.

Flags.Name: source-tls-mode
Flags.Description: The source TLS mode.

Flags.Name: source-cert-file
Flags.Description: The server certificate to present to the source client. For example 'myCert.pem'.

Flags.Name: source-key-file
Flags.Description: The server private key used to encrypt the server certificate. For example 'myKey.pem'.

Flags.Name: source-ca-cert-file
Flags.Description: Trusted CA certificate or chain used to validate the source client's certificate when source-tls-mode is mutual. For example 'myCA.pem'.

Flags.Name: q
Flags.Description: Do not show the message of the day or update reminders.

Flags.Name: s
Flags.Description: Do not show the message of the day or update reminders.
